Enum LineJoin

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LineJoin>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IconProvider, Serializable, Comparable<LineJoin>
    public enum LineJoin
extends Enum<LineJoin>
implements IconProvider
    An enumeration of the available line join styles used when drawing a path, such as when outlining a shape.
    Since:
    3.0
    Author:
    Chris Jennings

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      static class  LineJoin.LineJoinIcon  

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      BEVEL
      Joins path segments by connecting the outer corners of their wide outlines with a straight segment.
      MITER
      Joins path segments by extending their outside edges until they meet.
      ROUND
      Joins path segments by rounding off the corner at a radius of half the line width.
